==English==

===Etymology===
From [[black]] + [[list]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-blacklist.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''blacklist'''
#A [[list]] or collection of people or entities to [[shunned]] or [[banned]].
#:''The software included a lengthy '''blacklist''' of disreputable websites to block.''

===Translations===
:*Dutch: [[zwarte lijst]]

===Verb===
'''blacklist'''
#To place on a blacklist; to mark a person or entity as one to be shunned or banned.
#:''You can '''blacklist''' known spammers with that button.''

===See also===
*[[whitelist]]

